Natural history
. The spiders were found under rocks and in dry leaf litter in exposed habitats, in open spaces of dry forests and on roadsides (

). No specimens were found in neighboring, more forested and humid sites. Two egg-sacs contained four and 
five eggs
, respectively; egg diameters: 0.41–0.43. In glass vials, both males and females built small webs on which they were seen resting a few hours after being captured (

).

sec.p:
In Nicaragua , whose Pholcidae fauna is poorly known (currently only six species; see
,
,
), a high suitability area occurs in the Pacific Lowlands province (sensu
). In Panama , high suitability areas occur in coastal areas around the Gulf of Panama , far from the better sampled sites close to Panama City ( Fig. 35A ). In Venezuela , two discontinuous high suitability areas occur ( Fig. 35B ): (1) around the Gulf of Venezuela , a region that encompasses the Guajira-Barranquilla xeric scrubs, Paraguaná xeric scrubs and Lara- Falcón dry forests ecoregions; and (2) the Apure-Villavicencio dry forests and Llanos ecoregions (sensu
). By contrast, better sampled Venezuelan ecoregions (e.g., Maracaibo dry forests, Venezuelan Andes montane forests, La Costa xeric shrublands, and Cordillera La Costa montane forests) do not present any
Galapa
records or high environmental suitability. On the border between Peru and Ecuador , high suitability areas occur in the TumbesPiura and the Ecuadorian dry forests ecoregions ( Fig. 34A ). Finally, on the border between Brazil and Guiana , a high suitability area occurs in the Guianan savanna ecoregion ( Fig. 34A ).

Disregarding sampling biases, niche conservatism, and limited dispersal abilities, the current distribution of 

Galapa

might also represent a relict distribution or the effect of competitive exclusion. 
Ninetinae
represents an old lineage that may have emerged as early as the mid-Jurassic (

), when most of what is now South America, Africa, and southern North America was covered by dry environments (

). It is thus reasonable to speculate that ninetines had a wide distribution in the past, owing to their association with dry environments (
Fig. 36B
) and their niche conservatism (

). Through the Cretaceous and the Cenozoic, the environment shifted significantly throughout the Neotropical region, with the expansion of rainforests decreasing the availability of arid or semi-arid lands (

). Meanwhile, Pholcinae and Modisiminae (besides many other taxa with similar ecological requirements) occupied and thrived in the mesic environments, being the most diversified pholcids in the Neotropics (

). Competitive exclusion among pholcids has been reported for 

Galapa bella

, whose abundance appears negatively correlated with the abundance of 

Modisimus culicinus
(Simon, 1893)

, an introduced species in the 
Galapagos Islands
(

).
